      "span_text": "The bullwhip concept has its roots in Forrester's Industrial Dynamics [100] . Since the oscillating demand magnification upstream of a supply chain may resemble a cracking whip, it became famous as the bullwhip effect and is seen as one of the most important side effects of the lean environment [CITATION_1] ."
